entry.title: [WebUI] Migrate PrintManagementUI to WebUIConfig
entry.content:
This CL migrates PrintManagementUI to WebUIConfig. It also migrates

`BindPrintManagement` to PrintManagerFactory to de-clutter the

WebUIConfig registry.



Context:



Currently WebUI properties, e.g. CSPs, requesting schemes, host, mojo,

etc. are stored in WebUIControllers themselves or in separate lists

like IsWebUIAllowedToMakeNetworkRequests. The lifetime of a

WebUIController is bound to the frame, which makes it hard to use for

some use cases where the WebUIController hasn't been created yet. A

non-dynamically allocated class where clients could query a WebUI's

properties would be easier to use and audit.



WebUIConfig is a class that stores properties of WebUIs. For now the

properties are 1. the WebUI's origin, 2. if the WebUI is enabled,

and 3. GetURLDataSource() method for service worker initialization.

In the future this class could include information like CSPs, if we

should enable Mojo, if we should enable chrome.send(), if we should

allow network requests, URLDataSource, etc.



Bug: 1317510

entry.title: Fix flaky range-between-block-and-inline.html test
entry.content:
The range-between-block-and-inline.html test in question is flaky on

Mac platforms. The flakiness occurs because sometimes the test window

is inactive, leading to an inactive selection color (gray) versus the

expected active selection color (blue). This test is specifically

trying to test that the selection is painted in the right location, not the range positions in the DOM. Therefore, it has to remain a pixel test. Since there is no deterministic way to set the window as active from JS, the test is being fixed by setting the selection color

and background-color for active and inactive selection to be the same. This will ensure that the selection colors will always align with the baseline, regardless of whether the window is active or not.

entry.content:
Currently we send suggestions from the ime service to be displayed by

the system in the mojom call InputMethodHost::DisplaySuggestions(). This

method sends the suggestions without any other textual information.



This CL updates this method and adds a new optional param (for backwards

compat) preceding_text. This param contains the preceding text that was

used by the service to generate the suggestions given. This extra

context will allow consumers of the method to make a better decision as

to whether they should display the suggestions or not.

and supports a basic functionality for choosing a bluetooth device.

BluetoothChooserIOS::AddOrUpdateDevice() is called.

entry.title: [omnibox][doc] Display shorter URLs.
entry.content:
https://screenshot.googleplex.com/7ReyxdCrmUns4Dj



The remote doc response contains 2 URLs per document: `originalUrl` and

`url`.

- `originalUrl` is much shorter. E.g.

https://drive.google.com/a/google.com/open?id=&resourcekey=



- `url` is much longer. E.g.,

https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&esrc=s&source=

appssearch&uact=8&cd=0&cad=rja&q=&sig2=9NB3hPvQWP_8Z-

OMFJTsog&ved=0ahUKEwiB3e6Z_Ov-AhXxEvkAHZhmB0k4ABABKAAwAA&url

=https://drive.google.com/a/google.com/open%3Fid%3D

%26resourcekey%3D&usg=AOvVaw2q5Vrrjd92EfjX5jek6uxD



Currently,

- navigating (i.e. `destination_url`) uses the longer `url`.

- omnibox display (i.e. `fill_into_edit`) uses the longer `url`

- deduping (i.e. `stripped_destination_url`) uses the shorter

`originalUrl`.



With this CL, display will use the shorter `originalUrl`. Navigation

will continue to use `url`.



This allows copying doc URLs without having to navigate to them and wait

for the redirects to complete. Though the redirected final URL still

differs from the `originalUrl`.



This CL also has the `stripped_destination_url` fallback to use `url`

when `originalUrl` is empty.



Bug: 841265

entry.title: [fuchsia] Ensure services are not unintentionally offered from host component
entry.content:
Previously, CreateInstanceForContextWithCopiedArgs() would offer

services from the current Component, the `web_instance` host, iff no

`service_directory` was provided in the provided `CreateContextParams`.

This could lead to mistakes, like the one fixed by

https://crrev.com/c/4528805, or even abuse if no `service_directory`

or a partial `service_directory` was provided. Since the two modes are

for very different use cases, split them out into separate

sub-classes.



Bug: 1280703, 1421351
